SIMPLE: gratification
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gratification
<hw>Grat"i*fi*ca"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
gratificatio: cf. F. gratification.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of
gratifying, or pleasing, either the mind, the taste, or the appetite;
<as>as, the <ex>gratification</ex> of the palate, of the appetites, of
the senses, of the desires, of the heart</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which affords pleasure; satisfaction;
enjoyment; fruition: delight.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A reward; a recompense; a gratuity. </def>
<rj><au>Bp. Morton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gratified</ent>⟦br⟧
